The Amiga E Encyclopedia - A Concept

The Amiga E Encyclopedia (AEE) is an attempt to give E programmers a guide to
the AmigaOS. It is formed after the Amiga C Encyclopedia which consists of
texts, diagrams and examples.

Every function and structure of the OS is documented. There is a rich set of
examples, one-liners and complex ones.

There is also documentation about E-releated stuff such as memory allocation,
LISP-cells and OO. The implemented functions are also discussed - their usage
is shown as well as some hints are given. The Beginners.guide is not replaced,
this information is for the more experienced programmer.

The modules are documented in a more verbose fashion, too. Their authors will
be asked for additional information and examples.


I ask everybody to join the AEE - the more people the better. Everybody knows
at least a bit. As the title suggests, this is a concept. Literally anything
may - and will be - changed. Send your application today:)


